1
00:01:38,980 --> 00:01:41,800
[Episode 20]

2
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:44,621
You might've moved on,

3
00:01:44,621 --> 00:01:46,159
but I haven't.

4
00:01:46,159 --> 00:01:47,620
Cao Ping.

5
00:01:48,240 --> 00:01:49,720
Look forward.

6
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:52,360
Stop living on the past.

7
00:01:54,319 --> 00:01:56,360
From the day I went to prison,

8
00:01:56,360 --> 00:01:58,534
I did try to move on.

9
00:01:59,519 --> 00:02:02,120
For the past two years,
I've been straightening up

10
00:02:02,120 --> 00:02:05,088
to get out and reunite with my sister.

11
00:02:06,046 --> 00:02:07,909
What exactly do you want?

12
00:02:14,759 --> 00:02:16,800
Nothing.

13
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:18,520
You listen to me:

14
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:20,360
stay away from my sister.

15
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:23,600
Otherwise, I'll make life hard
for everyone around you.

16
00:02:29,039 --> 00:02:31,360
I never touched your sister.

17
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:33,040
Our beef is

18
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:34,360
between you and me.

19
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:36,383
If you've got guts, come at me.

20
00:02:38,599 --> 00:02:40,360
Stop fighting!

21
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:42,280
I'll call the police if you keep going!

22
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:43,960
Xing Wu!

23
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:48,840
Xing Wu,

24
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:50,680
We're not done yet.

25
00:02:56,960 --> 00:02:58,720
Who is he?

26
00:03:00,439 --> 00:03:02,560
An old acquaintance.

27
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:05,160
Why did you start fighting?

28
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,680
- It's nothing.
- You were about to brawl.

29
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:10,080
How is that nothing?

30
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:12,121
Before you came to Zhazhating,

31
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:14,533
I've got into plenty of

32
00:03:14,533 --> 00:03:16,599
fights and brawls.

33
00:03:16,599 --> 00:03:18,120
Xing Wu.

34
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:19,968
Xing Wu.

35
00:03:19,968 --> 00:03:21,440
If anything happens,

36
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:23,560
you must tell me.

37
00:03:57,199 --> 00:03:58,920
<i>Our beef is</i>

38
00:03:58,920 --> 00:04:00,360
<i>between you and me.</i>

39
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:02,319
<i>If you've got guts, come at me.</i>

40
00:04:02,319 --> 00:04:04,359
<i>Let my family alone.</i>

41
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:07,080
<i>That's too good for you.</i>

42
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:08,560
<i>Xing Wu,</i>

43
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:10,439
<i>as long as I'm alive,</i>

44
00:04:10,439 --> 00:04:12,680
<i>I'll never let you have peace.</i>

45
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:14,919
<i>I'm going to drag you</i>

46
00:04:14,919 --> 00:04:17,033
<i>through the mud I'm in.</i>

47
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:25,280
- Thank you.
- Auntie, I'll take it.

48
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:26,280
Okay.

49
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:28,470
Sent you the money.

50
00:04:30,199 --> 00:04:32,066
Let's go buy some meat.

51
00:04:32,066 --> 00:04:34,439
- What else do you want to eat?
- Anything is fine.

52
00:04:34,439 --> 00:04:35,639
Li, here.

53
00:04:35,639 --> 00:04:36,879
Fresh tenderloin. Take it?

54
00:04:36,879 --> 00:04:38,920
Fresh?

55
00:04:38,920 --> 00:04:40,399
- Then I want this one.
- All right.

56
00:04:40,399 --> 00:04:41,560
And two pork trotters.

57
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:43,240
Sure, no problem.

58
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:44,839
- Here you go.
- Okay, let me.

59
00:04:44,839 --> 00:04:46,640
Come back if you like it!

60
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:48,720
Grandma said

61
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:50,759
that you and Wu have been studying hard lately,

62
00:04:50,759 --> 00:04:53,319
so we need to make sure you eat well.

63
00:04:53,319 --> 00:04:54,353
Ye,

64
00:04:54,353 --> 00:04:56,471
why are you so distracted?

65
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:59,800
I'm fine.

66
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,881
It's Xing Wu.

67
00:05:04,079 --> 00:05:06,240
I feel like

68
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:09,080
he's always got something on mind.

69
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:12,279
Are you having a tiff?

70
00:05:12,279 --> 00:05:13,887
No.

71
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:17,800
I just don't get him sometimes.

72
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:18,845
Auntie,

73
00:05:18,845 --> 00:05:20,600
he's like a clam.

74
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:23,040
You know there's a stone inside,
rubbing against it,

75
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:25,045
but you just can't pry it open.

76
00:05:25,959 --> 00:05:27,639
Do you ever feel that way?

77
00:05:27,639 --> 00:05:30,120
Yes, of course I do.

78
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:31,439
When Wu was little,

79
00:05:31,439 --> 00:05:33,240
I had the energy to look after him.

80
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,618
I always wanted to know

81
00:05:34,618 --> 00:05:36,199
what was on his mind.

82
00:05:36,199 --> 00:05:38,012
I was afraid he was bottling everything up

83
00:05:38,012 --> 00:05:39,399
and hurting himself.

84
00:05:39,399 --> 00:05:40,567
When I was young,

85
00:05:40,567 --> 00:05:42,920
I wanted to be a good mom, too.

86
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:44,600
And then?

87
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:47,399
Later on, I couldn't even take care of myself.

88
00:05:47,399 --> 00:05:49,720
I had to think of paying off debts

89
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:51,399
and making ends meet.

90
00:05:51,399 --> 00:05:53,640
I had little time for him,

91
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:55,760
but he was low-maintenance.

92
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:58,079
They say the squeaky wheel gets the grease,

93
00:05:58,079 --> 00:06:00,439
but he never cried,

94
00:06:00,439 --> 00:06:02,279
and never asked me for anything.

95
00:06:02,279 --> 00:06:03,739
Over time,

96
00:06:03,739 --> 00:06:06,080
I just acted like nothing was wrong,

97
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:08,040
like everything was fine.

98
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:09,120
I got used to it.

99
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,880
Let's not dwell on that.

100
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:14,560
Come on, let's go get some yams.

101
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:16,000
Braised pork trotter with yams.

102
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,637
Wu's favorite.

103
00:06:27,879 --> 00:06:29,440
Your recent grades have been

104
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:31,720
like a roller coaster.

105
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:34,279
Dropped nearly a hundred points this time.

106
00:06:34,279 --> 00:06:35,579
You need to step it up

107
00:06:35,579 --> 00:06:37,594
on the next exam.

108
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:40,360
Don't worry, I know what I'm doing.

109
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:42,640
Cousin. Wu.

110
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:45,639
Don't you usually bike?

111
00:06:45,639 --> 00:06:47,160
Why take the bus?

112
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:48,959
Got a flat tire.

113
00:06:50,759 --> 00:06:52,439
It's been so windy lately.

114
00:06:52,439 --> 00:06:53,955
Can't be bothered to ride.

115
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:56,080
Plus, we can squeeze in

116
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:58,040
some vocab review on the way.

117
00:06:58,040 --> 00:07:00,839
Nice. Good to see you studying.

118
00:07:00,839 --> 00:07:03,240
Xing Wu, you can't afford to lose.

119
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:05,120
I won't.

120
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,640
I won't.

121
00:07:09,439 --> 00:07:10,759
What's that for?

122
00:07:10,759 --> 00:07:13,960
See if its location sharing still works.

123
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:15,395
Can't you just call me?

124
00:07:15,395 --> 00:07:17,160
What if it's an emergency?

125
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:19,099
Three taps are always easier.

126
00:07:25,839 --> 00:07:27,240
Let's go.

127
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:36,296
Wen Hui, have you heard?

128
00:07:36,296 --> 00:07:37,600
Cao Fan's brother did two years,

129
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:39,952
because he stabbed someone.

130
00:07:39,952 --> 00:07:40,960
Really?

131
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:43,399
- Don't just repeat rumors.
- That must be fake.

132
00:07:43,399 --> 00:07:45,393
Isn't her family pretty well off?

133
00:07:45,393 --> 00:07:47,120
She's always in the top three.

134
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:48,480
Think about it.

135
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:51,434
If it weren't true,
would everyone be talking about it?

136
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:53,480
So it has to be real.

137
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:55,279
People are giving all the details.

138
00:07:55,279 --> 00:07:57,319
They're even saying Xing Wu was involved.

139
00:07:57,319 --> 00:07:58,600
What does that mean?

140
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:00,519
I saw Cao Fan over the weekend.

141
00:08:00,519 --> 00:08:04,079
She was scrubbing shoes in a laundry.

142
00:08:04,079 --> 00:08:06,519
I went up to her and she got all shifty-eyed.

143
00:08:06,519 --> 00:08:08,760
She said her brother
runs a business in Shenzhen.

144
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:11,326
To me, he's an ex-con.

145
00:08:11,326 --> 00:08:14,400
No wonder her clothes have that laundry smell.

146
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:15,998
She claimed that her clothes

147
00:08:15,998 --> 00:08:18,920
were sent to the cleaners?

148
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:21,800
Who is she kidding, acting like a rich girl?

149
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:26,959
The only reason anyone

150
00:08:26,959 --> 00:08:28,058
hangs out with her is to copy her homework.

151
00:08:28,058 --> 00:08:30,152
Otherwise, who would?

152
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:34,240
Having a tea party here?

153
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:36,120
Why are you always showing up?

154
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,799
Did you hear everything?

155
00:08:37,799 --> 00:08:38,919
From which part?

156
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:41,120
The part about Cao Fan's brother,

157
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:43,279
or about herself?

158
00:08:43,279 --> 00:08:44,679
You were talking so loud,

159
00:08:44,679 --> 00:08:47,399
Why not just grab a loudspeaker
and let the whole school hear?

160
00:08:47,399 --> 00:08:48,840
So what if you heard us?

161
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:51,000
She spread the word about your dad before.

162
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,799
I was just getting back at her for you.

163
00:08:52,799 --> 00:08:54,519
Don't bother.

164
00:08:54,519 --> 00:08:56,000
You were right there

165
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,600
spreading those rumors yourself.

166
00:08:57,600 --> 00:09:00,400
Acting like you helped clear my name.

167
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:05,039
Just a friendly reminder:

168
00:09:05,039 --> 00:09:07,208
You two are tight with her now,

169
00:09:07,208 --> 00:09:09,420
but who knows what'll happen down the road?

170
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:20,399
You heard all that, didn't you?

171
00:09:20,399 --> 00:09:21,799
Now I'm everyone's target.

172
00:09:21,799 --> 00:09:23,080
That must make you happy.

173
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:24,440
I don't feel good about it.

174
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:26,519
It's never right and honorable
to attack someone

175
00:09:26,519 --> 00:09:28,120
over their family.

176
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:30,039
Every family has its ups and downs.

177
00:09:30,039 --> 00:09:32,893
We're students. We should focus on studying.

178
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:35,759
No one wants to be put
in the spotlight like that.

179
00:09:35,759 --> 00:09:37,639
Don't you agree?

180
00:09:37,639 --> 00:09:38,960
Mind your own business.

181
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:40,960
No one asked you to stand up for me.

182
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:43,360
I'm just speaking up for what's right,

183
00:09:43,360 --> 00:09:45,680
not for you.

184
00:09:48,639 --> 00:09:50,583
Your nose is bleeding.

185
00:09:51,167 --> 00:09:52,720
Here, tissue.

186
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:54,279
Don't pretend to care about me.

187
00:09:54,279 --> 00:09:56,120
We're not friends.

188
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,320
And,

189
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:02,919
you'd better not tell anyone
about Xing Wu and my brother.

190
00:10:02,919 --> 00:10:05,519
I don't want to get dragged into
whatever's between them.

191
00:10:05,519 --> 00:10:07,338
I owe you one for now.

192
00:10:07,919 --> 00:10:09,533
Between them?

193
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:15,720
<i>A boy at the competition</i>

194
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:17,480
<i>had it out for him,</i>

195
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:19,159
<i>and slashed him</i>

196
00:10:19,159 --> 00:10:20,800
<i>in the back</i>

197
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:22,120
<i>with a knife.</i>

198
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:23,640
<i>Cao Fan's brother did two years,</i>

199
00:10:23,640 --> 00:10:25,679
<i>because he stabbed someone.</i>

200
00:10:25,679 --> 00:10:28,200
<i>If it weren't true,
would everyone be talking about it?</i>

201
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:29,639
<i>So it has to be real.</i>

202
00:10:29,639 --> 00:10:32,560
<i>They're even saying Xing Wu was involved.</i>

203
00:10:35,720 --> 00:10:37,345
Isn't one camera by the entrance

204
00:10:37,345 --> 00:10:38,720
enough?

205
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:40,519
There's no need for an extra one inside.

206
00:10:40,519 --> 00:10:42,281
This brand's camera

207
00:10:42,281 --> 00:10:43,881
- isn't cheap.
- Nail.

208
00:10:43,881 --> 00:10:45,080
Wasting money.

209
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:46,440
Better safe than sorry.

210
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:48,399
Yang Gang has Cao Ping backing him now.

211
00:10:48,399 --> 00:10:49,399
They are going to

212
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:51,360
keep coming around, looking for trouble.

213
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,917
Last time, with all those people showing up,

214
00:10:52,917 --> 00:10:54,625
nothing serious happened.

215
00:10:54,625 --> 00:10:56,559
So don't be so tense.

216
00:10:56,559 --> 00:10:58,600
But what if one time I can't get here in time?

217
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:01,360
And things blow up?
An extra camera means extra protection,

218
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:03,324
and offers evidence to the police.

219
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:05,360
I'll be fine.

220
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:07,440
Cao Ping is after you, anyway.

221
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:08,480
If you need more hands,

222
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:09,840
you must tell us.

223
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:13,000
Hei and I are ready to ride with you anytime.

224
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:18,919
Ride? Ride for what?

225
00:11:18,919 --> 00:11:20,679
You've watched too many gangster movies.

226
00:11:20,679 --> 00:11:22,600
If your sister knew I got you into a fight,

227
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:24,759
she'd kill both of us.

228
00:11:24,759 --> 00:11:26,659
That's true.

229
00:11:27,279 --> 00:11:28,360
Sometimes,

230
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:30,562
fists don't solve anything.

231
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:34,232
If Cao Ping

232
00:11:34,232 --> 00:11:35,600
keeps messing with you,

233
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:37,560
what are you going to do?

234
00:11:39,879 --> 00:11:42,200
Don't worry about it.

235
00:11:46,039 --> 00:11:47,237
Hei.

236
00:11:47,799 --> 00:11:49,759
Wu, what's up?

237
00:11:49,759 --> 00:11:51,547
I've got exams coming up,

238
00:11:51,547 --> 00:11:54,320
so I probably
won't have much time to come to Shunyi Repair.

239
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:55,919
Kind of worried about leaving Canine alone.

240
00:11:55,919 --> 00:11:57,160
If you have some free time,

241
00:11:57,160 --> 00:11:58,600
could you keep an eye on him for me?

242
00:11:58,600 --> 00:12:00,720
Wu, you don't even have to ask. Don't worry.

243
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,679
The guys and I will drop whenever we can.

244
00:12:02,679 --> 00:12:03,799
Just focus on your studies

245
00:12:03,799 --> 00:12:05,519
and do well on the exams.

246
00:12:05,519 --> 00:12:06,679
Thanks.

247
00:12:06,679 --> 00:12:08,360
We're brothers. No need for thanks.

248
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:10,120
We all really envy you now.

249
00:12:10,120 --> 00:12:12,200
Look at you in that school uniform.

250
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,559
You look so sharp.

251
00:12:13,559 --> 00:12:14,679
People like us might never

252
00:12:14,679 --> 00:12:16,320
leave this little shop,

253
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:17,639
but you're different, Wu.

254
00:12:17,639 --> 00:12:18,720
You're smart.

255
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:20,080
You've got a mind for studying.

256
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:22,399
You fought your way back to school,

257
00:12:22,399 --> 00:12:24,044
so don't let the old garbage

258
00:12:24,044 --> 00:12:25,582
drag you down again.

259
00:12:26,892 --> 00:12:27,920
Don't worry.

260
00:12:27,920 --> 00:12:29,240
I know what I'm doing.

261
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:30,960
Go get them, Wu.

262
00:12:32,879 --> 00:12:34,603
I'm off.

263
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:40,084
Come on, eat up.

264
00:12:51,799 --> 00:12:53,559
Why the sudden skewers?

265
00:12:53,559 --> 00:12:55,328
I have something to ask you.

266
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:58,840
What is it?

267
00:12:59,919 --> 00:13:01,200
There's a rumor

268
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:03,120
going around school lately

269
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:05,432
that Cao Fan's brother

270
00:13:05,432 --> 00:13:07,080
just got out

271
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:08,639
after two years in jail.

272
00:13:08,639 --> 00:13:10,768
Have you heard it?

273
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:16,519
Xing Wu's sworn enemy

274
00:13:16,519 --> 00:13:19,000
is Cao Fan's brother, right?

275
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:20,836
I have no idea.

276
00:13:20,836 --> 00:13:22,799
Like there's any gossip I don't know?

277
00:13:22,799 --> 00:13:24,520
Must be fake.

278
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:26,520
Yeah.

279
00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:28,200
The scar on Xing Wu's back.

280
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:30,399
He got that from a knife two years ago,

281
00:13:30,399 --> 00:13:32,726
and the guy did two years for it.

282
00:13:33,399 --> 00:13:35,279
Just got out.

283
00:13:35,279 --> 00:13:36,720
Am I right?

284
00:13:40,143 --> 00:13:41,303
Not cooked yet.

285
00:13:41,303 --> 00:13:43,240
Xing Wu is afraid he'll come after me,

286
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:45,639
so he had you two shadow me.

287
00:13:45,639 --> 00:13:47,039
Right?

288
00:13:47,039 --> 00:13:49,159
This is bland. I'll get some dipping sauce.

289
00:13:49,159 --> 00:13:50,760
Feels like we don't have enough skewers.

290
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:52,640
I'll go get some more.

291
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:58,241
You two are terrible actors.

292
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:01,920
I can tell by your faces that I'm right.

293
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:07,519
<i>Sorry.</i>

294
00:14:07,519 --> 00:14:08,759
<i>The number you have dialed</i>

295
00:14:08,759 --> 00:14:10,931
<i>is temporarily unavailable.</i>

296
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:21,159
<i>Sorry.</i>

297
00:14:21,159 --> 00:14:23,280
<i>The number you have dialed...</i>

298
00:14:26,120 --> 00:14:27,200
<i>Sorry.</i>

299
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:29,520
<i>The number you have dialed...</i>

300
00:14:35,668 --> 00:14:37,392
[Lighthouse by the sea]
[Distance: 8.5 km]

301
00:14:40,559 --> 00:14:41,960
<i>Qing Ye found out about your beef
with Cao Ping.</i>

302
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:44,200
- Qing Ye!
<i>- She didn't let us follow her.</i>

303
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:46,720
<i>- I'm worried she might go find him.</i>
- Qing Ye!

304
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:51,776
Qing Ye!

305
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:54,360
You...

306
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:56,559
Why are you so out of breath?

307
00:15:56,559 --> 00:15:58,360
Sorry.

308
00:15:58,360 --> 00:16:00,360
Just let me hold you for a minute.

309
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,760
My phone died.

310
00:16:11,519 --> 00:16:13,720
Right before it shut off,

311
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:16,320
I saw you'd called me,

312
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:19,200
so I sent you my location.

313
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:21,720
I didn't realize

314
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:24,249
it would make you think I was in danger.

315
00:16:34,440 --> 00:16:36,401
I'm just glad you're okay.

316
00:16:42,232 --> 00:16:43,559
Actually,

317
00:16:43,559 --> 00:16:45,240
after I sent the location,

318
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:47,120
for a split second,

319
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:48,600
I thought about

320
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:51,600
faking an emergency,

321
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:53,960
let you not find me,

322
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:56,159
so you'd know what it's like

323
00:16:56,159 --> 00:16:58,520
to wait for an answer that never comes.

324
00:17:01,519 --> 00:17:04,000
But then I figured,

325
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:06,000
forget it.

326
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,040
Either way,

327
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:11,720
you have the right to keep your secrets.

328
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:20,720
Then I'll tell you

329
00:17:20,720 --> 00:17:22,760
what happened two years ago.

330
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:30,160
Two years ago,

331
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:32,519
Xing Guo Dong mortgaged Xuan Island.

332
00:17:32,519 --> 00:17:34,044
We were buried in debt.

333
00:17:34,044 --> 00:17:35,960
Grandma was in the hospital

334
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:37,720
and we desperately needed money.

335
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:42,039
So I decided
to enter the city basketball tournament.

336
00:17:42,039 --> 00:17:44,200
If I won the MVP award,

337
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:46,055
there'd be a cash prize.

338
00:17:46,055 --> 00:17:48,379
[Lianhai City Future Star High School
Basketball League]

339
00:17:48,379 --> 00:17:49,680
[Attack Team vs. Xuan Island Team]

340
00:17:49,680 --> 00:17:53,000
<i>Xuan Island! Xuan Island! We're the best!</i>

341
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:54,480
<i>Xuan Island! Xuan Island!</i>

342
00:17:54,480 --> 00:17:56,319
<i>Xing Wu! Xing Wu!</i>

343
00:17:56,319 --> 00:17:58,039
<i>Xing Wu! Xing Wu!</i>

344
00:17:58,039 --> 00:17:59,840
Cao Ping was also

345
00:17:59,840 --> 00:18:01,519
in that tournament.

346
00:18:01,519 --> 00:18:03,279
At that time, he was at a vocational school.

347
00:18:03,279 --> 00:18:04,952
In his third year.

348
00:18:05,599 --> 00:18:07,240
For him,

349
00:18:07,240 --> 00:18:09,519
winning that tournament

350
00:18:09,519 --> 00:18:12,088
was his last shot to be recruited
into a sports academy.

351
00:18:13,119 --> 00:18:15,079
But he had an Achilles tendon injury.

352
00:18:15,079 --> 00:18:16,559
<i>Xuan Island! Xuan Island!</i>

353
00:18:16,559 --> 00:18:18,119
<i>Attack! Attack!</i>

354
00:18:18,119 --> 00:18:20,160
<i>Conquer the world!</i>

355
00:18:20,160 --> 00:18:21,559
<i>Attack! Attack!</i>

356
00:18:21,559 --> 00:18:24,200
<i>Ping, how's your foot?</i>

357
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:25,240
<i>I'm fine.</i>

358
00:18:25,240 --> 00:18:27,240
<i>We have to give it our all. You hear me?</i>

359
00:18:27,240 --> 00:18:28,400
<i>Given how good you are,</i>

360
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:29,400
<i>even injured,</i>

361
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:31,839
<i>MVP title won't be a problem. Right?</i>

362
00:18:31,839 --> 00:18:33,680
<i>It's really down to all of us.</i>

363
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:35,319
<i>Xuan Island! Xuan Island!</i>

364
00:18:35,319 --> 00:18:36,960
<i>Attack! Attack!</i>

365
00:18:36,960 --> 00:18:38,599
<i>Xuan Island! Xuan Island!</i>

366
00:18:38,599 --> 00:18:40,519
<i>Attack! Attack!</i>

367
00:18:40,519 --> 00:18:42,240
<i>Xuan Island! Xuan Island!</i>

368
00:18:42,240 --> 00:18:43,920
<i>We're the best!</i>

369
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:46,600
<i>Xuan Island! Xuan Island!</i>

370
00:19:02,319 --> 00:19:04,014
<i>Go for it!</i>

371
00:19:19,559 --> 00:19:21,615
<i>Nice shot! Xuan Island scores again!</i>

372
00:19:21,615 --> 00:19:22,628
<i>That's Xing Wu?</i>

373
00:19:22,628 --> 00:19:24,160
<i>As a rookie, he's unstoppable.</i>

374
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:25,240
<i>A force to be reckoned with!</i>

375
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:26,960
<i>What a dark horse!</i>

376
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:27,960
<i>Attack's Cao Ping</i>

377
00:19:27,960 --> 00:19:30,119
<i>has really met his match this time.</i>

378
00:19:30,119 --> 00:19:33,572
<i>I wonder if his MVP title might slip away.</i>

379
00:19:38,160 --> 00:19:40,680
<i>Go! Go! Go!</i>

380
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:44,080
<i>Go! Go! Go!</i>

381
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:48,019
<i>Go! Go! Go!</i>

382
00:20:07,519 --> 00:20:11,560
<i>Go! Go! Go!</i>

383
00:20:11,560 --> 00:20:15,544
<i>Go! Go! Go!</i>

384
00:20:19,359 --> 00:20:21,080
<i>Are you okay?</i>

385
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:44,119
<i>Xing Wu!</i>

386
00:20:44,119 --> 00:20:45,359
<i>Let's congratulate Xing Wu</i>

387
00:20:45,359 --> 00:20:46,359
<i>for winning the title of</i>

388
00:20:46,359 --> 00:20:48,640
<i>Most Valuable Player in this year's league!</i>

389
00:20:48,640 --> 00:20:49,880
<i>Congratulations to Xuan Island!</i>

390
00:20:49,880 --> 00:20:53,599
<i>Xuan Island! Xuan Island! Xuan Island!</i>

391
00:20:53,599 --> 00:20:56,359
<i>Xuan Island! Xuan Island! Xuan Island!</i>

392
00:20:56,359 --> 00:20:59,079
<i>Xuan Island! Xuan Island! Xuan Island!</i>

393
00:20:59,079 --> 00:21:01,839
<i>Xuan Island! Xuan Island! Xuan Island!</i>

394
00:21:01,839 --> 00:21:06,599
<i>Xuan Island! Xuan Island! Xuan Island!</i>

395
00:21:06,599 --> 00:21:08,920
<i>Congrats to Wu for getting MVP!</i>

396
00:21:08,920 --> 00:21:09,946
<i>And the prize money!</i>

397
00:21:09,946 --> 00:21:12,281
<i>Xuan Island champs!</i>

398
00:21:16,119 --> 00:21:18,120
<i>Order whatever you want tonight.</i>

399
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:19,163
<i>It's on me.</i>

400
00:21:19,163 --> 00:21:20,759
<i>Really?</i>

401
00:21:20,759 --> 00:21:22,855
<i>Have I ever lied to you?</i>

402
00:21:22,855 --> 00:21:23,880
<i>Hello!</i>

403
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:25,279
<i>20 kidney skewers!</i>

404
00:21:25,279 --> 00:21:26,960
<i>And 20 pork fat skewers!</i>

405
00:21:26,960 --> 00:21:28,279
<i>Coming right up!</i>

406
00:21:28,279 --> 00:21:30,519
<i>Neither of you is leaving until you finish.</i>

407
00:21:30,519 --> 00:21:33,079
<i>Hi, 20 meat skewers. Whatever else looks good.</i>

408
00:21:33,079 --> 00:21:35,653
<i>Got it. One sec.</i>

409
00:21:35,653 --> 00:21:36,720
<i>Wu,</i>

410
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:38,342
<i>Cao Ping is coming over.</i>

411
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:42,519
<i>Look at that loser face.</i>

412
00:21:42,519 --> 00:21:44,520
<i>Definitely salty about the loss.</i>

413
00:21:45,360 --> 00:21:46,768
<i>Another toast to Wu.</i>

414
00:21:46,768 --> 00:21:48,281
<i>Cheers!</i>

415
00:21:52,360 --> 00:21:54,040
<i>Xing Wu.</i>

416
00:21:54,040 --> 00:21:55,400
<i>Congrats on the win</i>

417
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:57,645
<i>and on getting MVP today.</i>

418
00:21:58,880 --> 00:22:01,039
<i>I know your leg is injured.</i>

419
00:22:01,039 --> 00:22:04,000
<i>Otherwise,</i>

420
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:06,119
<i>maybe you would have been the MVP.</i>

421
00:22:06,119 --> 00:22:08,400
<i>I heard not only did you get the prize money,</i>

422
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:10,319
<i>but a provincial team coach</i>

423
00:22:10,319 --> 00:22:11,519
<i>came to recruit you.</i>

424
00:22:11,519 --> 00:22:14,119
<i>I'm not up for that.</i>

425
00:22:14,119 --> 00:22:15,519
<i>Being a pro athlete is not for me.</i>

426
00:22:15,519 --> 00:22:17,400
<i>I just need the money.</i>

427
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:18,759
<i>Don't give me that.</i>

428
00:22:18,759 --> 00:22:20,839
<i>Can't you stand up when you talk to Ping?</i>

429
00:22:20,839 --> 00:22:21,880
<i>Do you know how hard</i>

430
00:22:21,880 --> 00:22:23,720
<i>Ping risked for this tournament?</i>

431
00:22:23,720 --> 00:22:24,759
<i>Risked his life for what?</i>

432
00:22:24,759 --> 00:22:26,359
<i>So he hurt his leg. What a big deal!</i>

433
00:22:26,359 --> 00:22:28,640
<i>He's standing here with all his limbs.</i>

434
00:22:28,640 --> 00:22:30,160
<i>You want to join the provincial team?</i>

435
00:22:30,160 --> 00:22:31,400
<i>Go talk to the coach yourselves.</i>

436
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:32,880
<i>Wu has zero interest</i>

437
00:22:32,880 --> 00:22:34,279
<i>in the provincial team at all.</i>

438
00:22:34,279 --> 00:22:35,680
<i>What's your angle? Looking for a fight?</i>

439
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:36,920
<i>I'm not looking for a fight.</i>

440
00:22:36,920 --> 00:22:38,837
<i>I'm just telling the truth. What's wrong?</i>

441
00:22:38,837 --> 00:22:40,160
<i>The truth is not allowed?</i>

442
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:42,279
<i>A leg injury doesn't make him a cripple.</i>

443
00:22:42,279 --> 00:22:43,920
<i>- Don't start something, okay?
- Hey, you...</i>

444
00:22:43,920 --> 00:22:45,240
<i>All you've got is hitting?</i>

445
00:22:45,240 --> 00:22:46,680
<i>What's your problem?</i>

446
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:48,119
<i>Don't make me do it.</i>

447
00:22:48,119 --> 00:22:49,839
<i>That's enough, both of you.</i>

448
00:22:49,839 --> 00:22:51,759
<i>My buddy's got a big mouth.</i>

449
00:22:51,759 --> 00:22:53,360
<i>Sorry about that.</i>

450
00:22:53,960 --> 00:22:55,359
<i>I'll toast you.</i>

451
00:22:55,359 --> 00:22:56,960
<i>Hold on.</i>

452
00:22:58,839 --> 00:23:00,520
<i>Use this instead.</i>

453
00:23:02,519 --> 00:23:04,200
<i>Exactly. Who do you think you are?</i>

454
00:23:04,200 --> 00:23:05,519
<i>This is how you toast Ping?</i>

455
00:23:05,519 --> 00:23:07,000
<i>Am I being too easy on you?</i>

456
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:08,440
<i>- What's your problem?
- Don't push me!</i>

457
00:23:08,440 --> 00:23:10,039
<i>- What do you mean?
- Nothing.</i>

458
00:23:10,039 --> 00:23:11,359
<i>Try me. Make my day.</i>

459
00:23:11,359 --> 00:23:12,759
<i>Lay a hand on me and I'll drop to the ground.</i>

460
00:23:12,759 --> 00:23:13,920
<i>My parents will be getting a new car out of it.</i>

461
00:23:13,920 --> 00:23:14,920
<i>Try me!</i>

462
00:23:14,920 --> 00:23:16,720
<i>By the way, Cao Ping.</i>

463
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:19,440
<i>Provincial teams don't take gimps, do they?</i>

464
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:21,320
<i>You asked for it!</i>

465
00:23:36,079 --> 00:23:37,519
<i>Come on!</i>

466
00:23:37,519 --> 00:23:38,920
<i>Fuzz!</i>

467
00:23:59,680 --> 00:24:00,960
<i>Cao Ping.</i>

468
00:24:00,960 --> 00:24:02,599
<i>I have no intention of</i>

469
00:24:02,599 --> 00:24:04,239
<i>joining the provincial team.</i>

470
00:24:19,759 --> 00:24:21,480
<i>Xing Wu!</i>

471
00:24:25,079 --> 00:24:26,720
<i>Wu!</i>

472
00:24:30,359 --> 00:24:31,920
<i>Wu!</i>

473
00:24:31,920 --> 00:24:33,759
<i>Call 120, quick!</i>

474
00:24:33,759 --> 00:24:35,160
<i>Anyone!</i>

475
00:24:35,160 --> 00:24:37,280
<i>Call an ambulance!</i>

476
00:25:03,440 --> 00:25:06,079
Cao Ping lost it

477
00:25:06,079 --> 00:25:08,200
and slashed me in the back.

478
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:10,000
He got two years.

479
00:25:16,680 --> 00:25:18,240
If

480
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:20,232
that hadn't happened,

481
00:25:21,279 --> 00:25:23,840
you would've become a pilot, right?

482
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:31,008
Maybe it's fate.

483
00:25:31,839 --> 00:25:33,880
I thought

484
00:25:33,880 --> 00:25:35,960
I was so close to my dream.

485
00:25:38,880 --> 00:25:40,840
<i>Take off your shirt.</i>

486
00:25:50,359 --> 00:25:52,051
<i>Turn around.</i>

487
00:26:04,519 --> 00:26:06,320
<i>Xing Wu.</i>

488
00:26:08,799 --> 00:26:10,643
<i>You can go now.</i>

489
00:26:20,720 --> 00:26:22,880
I once heard someone say

490
00:26:22,880 --> 00:26:25,599
that the days crushed by pain

491
00:26:25,599 --> 00:26:27,240
are like

492
00:26:27,240 --> 00:26:29,599
the mud after the tide goes out.

493
00:26:29,599 --> 00:26:30,746
It looks messy,

494
00:26:30,746 --> 00:26:31,800
but

495
00:26:31,800 --> 00:26:33,960
when the sun rises,

496
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:36,039
the shell fragments

497
00:26:36,039 --> 00:26:38,120
hidden within it shimmer.

498
00:26:38,120 --> 00:26:39,960
That shimmer

499
00:26:39,960 --> 00:26:42,559
becomes the mark

500
00:26:42,559 --> 00:26:44,571
of your life.

501
00:26:49,960 --> 00:26:50,977
We all have

502
00:26:50,977 --> 00:26:53,720
our own path to follow.

503
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:55,519
Take me,

504
00:26:55,519 --> 00:26:57,240
I thought I'd be

505
00:26:57,240 --> 00:26:58,599
studying abroad by now.

506
00:26:58,599 --> 00:27:00,280
Look at me instead.

507
00:27:03,079 --> 00:27:05,160
Still, I'm not bitter.

508
00:27:05,160 --> 00:27:07,440
Fate brought me here,

509
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:09,359
to live a different life

510
00:27:09,359 --> 00:27:11,480
in Zhazhating.

511
00:27:13,039 --> 00:27:15,233
In fact, I'm grateful.

512
00:27:16,119 --> 00:27:18,960
Because every second here

513
00:27:20,240 --> 00:27:23,000
has made my youth burn brighter.

514
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:52,640
Anyway...

515
00:27:52,640 --> 00:27:53,759
it's getting late.

516
00:27:53,759 --> 00:27:55,600
Let's head back.

517
00:28:03,039 --> 00:28:04,880
Good luck

518
00:28:05,559 --> 00:28:07,160
on your test tomorrow.

519
00:28:08,400 --> 00:28:09,400
Don't worry.

520
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:11,440
I've got this.

521
00:28:15,200 --> 00:28:16,600
Come on.

522
00:28:37,559 --> 00:28:39,400
- Over there.
- Okay.

523
00:28:50,319 --> 00:28:53,319
She has been on her own a lot lately.

524
00:28:53,319 --> 00:28:55,119
Studying while eating?

525
00:28:55,119 --> 00:28:57,080
Look at her showing off.

526
00:28:57,880 --> 00:28:59,559
Such a prig.

527
00:28:59,559 --> 00:29:01,880
If she can't even get selected after all that,

528
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:04,480
I'd be embarrassed for her.

529
00:29:05,640 --> 00:29:06,799
She's hitting the books.

530
00:29:06,799 --> 00:29:08,480
Keep it up.

531
00:29:08,480 --> 00:29:10,640
Keep grinding and she still can't beat Qing Ye.

532
00:29:10,640 --> 00:29:12,079
You go ahead. I'll be right back.

533
00:29:12,079 --> 00:29:13,640
Let's just watch.

534
00:29:13,640 --> 00:29:16,280
She's so insufferable.

535
00:29:23,279 --> 00:29:24,897
Why are you staring at us?

536
00:29:28,920 --> 00:29:30,000
What's up?

537
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:31,680
Eat.

538
00:29:32,319 --> 00:29:35,039
Your food is getting cold.

539
00:29:35,039 --> 00:29:36,600
None of your business.

540
00:29:37,599 --> 00:29:40,279
You don't look well.

541
00:29:40,279 --> 00:29:42,400
Are you okay?

542
00:29:42,400 --> 00:29:44,478
Mind your own business.

543
00:29:54,880 --> 00:29:57,520
All right, begin.

544
00:31:12,119 --> 00:31:13,279
Teacher! Teacher!

545
00:31:13,279 --> 00:31:15,119
Cao Fan fainted!

546
00:31:15,119 --> 00:31:16,519
Cao Fan! What's wrong?

547
00:31:16,519 --> 00:31:17,880
Cao Fan! Cao Fan!

548
00:31:17,880 --> 00:31:19,360
Can you hear me?

549
00:31:24,984 --> 00:31:27,484
[Emergency]

550
00:31:37,759 --> 00:31:38,960
Hello? What's up?

551
00:31:38,960 --> 00:31:40,519
<i>Ping, bad news.</i>

552
00:31:40,519 --> 00:31:42,440
<i>You told me to keep an eye on your sister.</i>

553
00:31:42,440 --> 00:31:44,319
<i>She's unconscious at the county hospital.</i>

554
00:31:44,319 --> 00:31:45,519
<i>Doesn't look good.</i>

555
00:31:45,519 --> 00:31:46,680
<i>Xing Wu and his cousin</i>

556
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:47,880
<i>brought her in.</i>

557
00:31:47,880 --> 00:31:50,773
<i>I bet they have something to do with it.</i>

558
00:31:52,280 --> 00:31:54,039
Doctor,

559
00:31:54,039 --> 00:31:56,400
how is she?

560
00:31:56,400 --> 00:31:57,720
38.9 degrees.

561
00:31:57,720 --> 00:31:58,920
That's a high fever.

562
00:31:58,920 --> 00:32:00,279
We ran a blood test.

563
00:32:00,279 --> 00:32:02,000
She has low blood sugar,

564
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:03,240
some malnutrition,

565
00:32:03,240 --> 00:32:05,559
and her nosebleed is from dry nasal membranes.

566
00:32:05,559 --> 00:32:07,319
Clearly, she's been staying up late

567
00:32:07,319 --> 00:32:08,701
and not getting enough rest.

568
00:32:08,701 --> 00:32:11,640
Doctor, when will she wake up?

569
00:32:11,640 --> 00:32:13,599
Given her condition, she's still very weak.

570
00:32:13,599 --> 00:32:15,720
But nothing too serious.

571
00:32:15,720 --> 00:32:17,640
Let her rest.

572
00:32:17,640 --> 00:32:19,342
- Page me if anything comes up.
- Okay.

573
00:32:19,342 --> 00:32:21,249
Thank you very much.

574
00:32:23,519 --> 00:32:24,640
Mr. Zhu,

575
00:32:24,640 --> 00:32:26,079
how about you head back to school?

576
00:32:26,079 --> 00:32:28,559
We'll stay with her.

577
00:32:28,559 --> 00:32:29,720
All right.

578
00:32:29,720 --> 00:32:31,000
I'll come to relieve you

579
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:32,400
after evening self-study.

580
00:32:32,400 --> 00:32:34,911
- Okay.
- Thank you, Xing Wu.

581
00:32:38,479 --> 00:32:39,520
I could tell something

582
00:32:39,520 --> 00:32:42,359
was off with her before the exam.

583
00:32:42,359 --> 00:32:44,880
I should've told the teacher sooner.

584
00:32:45,519 --> 00:32:46,920
Don't overthink it.

585
00:32:46,920 --> 00:32:48,240
The doctor just said

586
00:32:48,240 --> 00:32:49,640
it's nothing serious.

587
00:32:49,640 --> 00:32:51,160
Don't worry.

588
00:32:52,599 --> 00:32:54,640
I'll go get you something to eat.

589
00:34:37,239 --> 00:34:39,440
You're awake.

590
00:34:39,440 --> 00:34:41,680
How are you feeling? Any better?

591
00:34:51,000 --> 00:34:53,400
Here's a thermos.
Weren't you looking for one earlier?

592
00:34:53,400 --> 00:34:54,719
Take it for now.

593
00:34:54,719 --> 00:34:55,720
Thank you.

594
00:34:55,720 --> 00:34:57,360
The water room is over there.

595
00:34:57,360 --> 00:34:59,600
- I can go by myself.
- Okay.

596
00:35:02,639 --> 00:35:04,600
I know you blame me.

597
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:09,160
I haven't been a good brother.

598
00:35:10,639 --> 00:35:12,920
You have every reason to ignore me.

599
00:35:20,559 --> 00:35:23,400
If anyone bullies you at school,
remember to tell me.

600
00:35:25,280 --> 00:35:26,989
And then what?

601
00:35:32,199 --> 00:35:34,920
Are you going to start a fight
like you did before?

602
00:35:34,920 --> 00:35:36,119
Plenty of people have bullied me.

603
00:35:36,119 --> 00:35:38,117
Can you fight them all?

604
00:35:43,639 --> 00:35:44,840
Just leave.

605
00:35:44,840 --> 00:35:46,760
I can't sleep with you here.

606
00:35:50,800 --> 00:35:52,560
Take care of yourself.

607
00:36:29,119 --> 00:36:31,400
<i>Xing Wu and his cousin brought her in.</i>

608
00:36:31,400 --> 00:36:34,320
<i>I guarantee they're involved.</i>

609
00:36:34,320 --> 00:36:35,440
<i>Plenty of people have bullied me.</i>

610
00:36:35,440 --> 00:36:37,360
<i>Can you fight them all?</i>

611
00:37:01,559 --> 00:37:03,240
Where do you think you're going?

612
00:37:05,599 --> 00:37:08,880
You're Cao Fan's brother, Cao Ping, right?

613
00:37:08,880 --> 00:37:10,559
I think you've got it wrong.

614
00:37:10,559 --> 00:37:12,079
Cao Fan and I aren't enemies.

615
00:37:12,079 --> 00:37:14,119
Save your excuses.

616
00:37:14,119 --> 00:37:17,400
My sister ended up like this

617
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:19,519
because of you and your brother.

618
00:37:19,519 --> 00:37:21,731
You've got it wrong.

619
00:37:22,360 --> 00:37:23,800
This is a hospital.

620
00:37:23,800 --> 00:37:26,000
People will come by any minute.

621
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:28,400
You'd better calm down.

622
00:37:39,840 --> 00:37:41,920
You think I care about that?

623
00:37:46,199 --> 00:37:49,200
Your sister didn't faint because of me.

624
00:37:50,120 --> 00:37:51,760
We were taking an exam.

625
00:37:51,760 --> 00:37:54,400
She suddenly started sweating a lot,

626
00:37:54,400 --> 00:37:56,840
and then she collapsed.

627
00:38:02,375 --> 00:38:04,675
[Anzi County First People's Hospital]
[Distance: 500m]

628
00:38:05,531 --> 00:38:08,400
Young man, your fried rice!

629
00:38:08,400 --> 00:38:09,519
Let go of me!

630
00:38:09,519 --> 00:38:11,640
- Let go!
- Who are you trying to call?

631
00:38:20,119 --> 00:38:22,480
Don't be afraid. I'm here.

632
00:38:30,159 --> 00:38:31,719
You go back first.

633
00:38:31,719 --> 00:38:33,760
I'll talk to him.

634
00:38:33,760 --> 00:38:35,639
No way. But...

635
00:38:35,639 --> 00:38:37,639
Don't worry.

636
00:38:37,639 --> 00:38:39,760
I know what I'm doing.

637
00:38:39,760 --> 00:38:41,199
Go back.

638
00:38:41,199 --> 00:38:42,800
Okay.

639
00:38:42,800 --> 00:38:44,840
I'll go back.

640
00:38:44,840 --> 00:38:47,560
If you aren't back in ten minutes,

641
00:38:48,239 --> 00:38:50,160
I'm calling the police.

642
00:38:51,920 --> 00:38:53,680
Just go back.

643
00:39:14,160 --> 00:39:16,934
I told you not to touch my family.

644
00:39:17,880 --> 00:39:19,640
Got some fight in you.

645
00:39:20,280 --> 00:39:22,305
What if I insist on messing with them?

646
00:39:22,305 --> 00:39:24,320
What do you want?

647
00:39:24,320 --> 00:39:26,519
Simple.

648
00:39:26,519 --> 00:39:28,640
I want you to lose

649
00:39:28,640 --> 00:39:30,440
everyone as I did.

650
00:39:30,440 --> 00:39:32,120
Then I'll be satisfied.

651
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:35,244
Then come at me.

652
00:39:47,119 --> 00:39:48,960
Three days,

653
00:39:48,960 --> 00:39:51,040
we'll settle this once and for all.

654
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:55,038
Fine.

655
00:40:13,280 --> 00:40:15,000
Sit here.

656
00:40:15,760 --> 00:40:17,239
Hello,

657
00:40:17,239 --> 00:40:18,440
two more orders of fried rice.

658
00:40:18,440 --> 00:40:19,920
- No green onions, mild spice.
- Got it.

659
00:40:19,920 --> 00:40:21,599
And add that last order to my tab, too.

660
00:40:21,599 --> 00:40:23,000
- Sure.
- Add an egg to one of them.

661
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:25,000
Alright, no problem.

662
00:40:29,840 --> 00:40:31,519
Are you hurt?

663
00:40:31,519 --> 00:40:33,160
No.

664
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:44,080
You got scared, didn't you?

665
00:40:49,159 --> 00:40:51,920
It's my fault for dragging you into this.

666
00:40:53,679 --> 00:40:56,080
I didn't lose anything.

667
00:40:58,239 --> 00:41:00,280
How did it go with him?

668
00:41:01,360 --> 00:41:04,197
Nothing. It's fine.

669
00:41:04,197 --> 00:41:05,640
Don't worry.

670
00:41:05,640 --> 00:41:07,560
I'll handle it.

671
00:42:15,559 --> 00:42:16,719
<i>What brings you here?</i>

672
00:42:16,719 --> 00:42:18,125
<i>Brought your meal.</i>

673
00:42:18,125 --> 00:42:19,774
<i>What'd you make me?</i>

674
00:42:19,774 --> 00:42:21,440
<i>Dumplings, red braised pork belly,</i>

675
00:42:21,440 --> 00:42:23,378
<i>and some other dishes.</i>

676
00:42:23,378 --> 00:42:24,600
<i>All your favorites.</i>

677
00:42:24,600 --> 00:42:26,813
<i>Wait for me a moment.</i>

678
00:42:29,520 --> 00:42:32,280
<i>- Brother...
- Why are you staring at me like that?</i>

679
00:42:32,280 --> 00:42:34,679
<i>I'm eyeing a watch.</i>

680
00:42:34,679 --> 00:42:36,199
<i>It looks really cool.</i>

681
00:42:36,199 --> 00:42:37,360
<i>A watch?</i>

682
00:42:37,360 --> 00:42:39,360
<i>What do you need a watch for?</i>

683
00:42:39,360 --> 00:42:41,440
<i>- Well...
- Alright, let me see.</i>

684
00:42:41,440 --> 00:42:43,200
<i>Let me see the page.</i>

685
00:42:43,840 --> 00:42:45,320
<i>This one.</i>

686
00:42:45,320 --> 00:42:47,160
<i>It does look nice.</i>

687
00:42:49,599 --> 00:42:51,599
<i>Fine. After I win the tournament,</i>

688
00:42:51,599 --> 00:42:53,480
<i>I'll buy it with the prize money.</i>

689
00:43:15,132 --> 00:43:17,120
Are you being discharged?

690
00:43:17,120 --> 00:43:19,519
Don't act as if you know me.

691
00:43:19,519 --> 00:43:20,519
I owe you one for yesterday.

692
00:43:20,519 --> 00:43:22,119
I'll find a way to pay you back.

693
00:43:22,119 --> 00:43:23,639
How about you owe me another favor,

694
00:43:23,639 --> 00:43:25,680
and make it a big one next time?

695
00:43:26,639 --> 00:43:28,803
What do you mean?

696
00:43:28,803 --> 00:43:30,960
Go to the Winter Camp.

697
00:43:30,960 --> 00:43:33,160
Are you giving me your spot?

698
00:43:34,519 --> 00:43:36,519
But I have one condition:

699
00:43:36,519 --> 00:43:39,029
Help your brother and Xing Wu make peace.

